                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Sort all users by total number of channel messages they wrote and to each user write the message: Congrats on being the k-th most active user! (where k is replaced with the user's rank). Resolve ties alphabetically."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "\n```python\n# Step 1: Get all channels\nchannels = get_channels()\n\n# Step 2: Collect all messages from all channels\nall_messages = []\nfor channel in channels:\n    msgs = read_channel_messages(channel)\n    all_messages = all_messages + msgs\n\n# Step 3: Collect all users that appear in any channel\nall_users = set()\nfor channel in channels:\n    users_in_channel = get_users_in_channel(channel)\n    all_users = all_users | set(users_in_channel)\n\n# Step 4: Count messages per user based on channel messages\nmessage_counts = {}\nfor msg in all_messages:\n    message_counts[msg.sender] = message_counts.get(msg.sender, 0) + 1\n\n# Make sure every user has a count (defaulting to 0 if they wrote no messages)\nfinal_counts = {user: message_counts.get(user, 0) for user in all_users}\n\n# Step 5: Sort users by descending count, then alphabetically for ties\nsorted_pairs = sorted([(-final_counts[user], user) for user in all_users])\n\n# Step 6: Send a direct message to each user with their rank\nfor idx, pair in enumerate(sorted_pairs):\n    rank = idx + 1\n    user = pair[1]\n    message_body = f\"Congrats on being the {rank}-th most active user!\"\n    send_direct_message(user, message_body)\n\nprint(\"Messages sent to all users based on their channel activity ranking.\")\n```"
                }
